    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\n:checkhealth vim.lsp\n```\nvim.lsp: Enabled Configurations ~\n- ⚠️ WARNING Unknown filetype 'yaml.ansible' (Hint: filename extension != filetype).\n- ansiblels:\n  - cmd: { \"ansible-language-server\", \"--stdio\" }\n  - filetypes: yaml.ansible\n  - root_markers: { \"ansible.cfg\", \".ansible-lint\" }\n  - settings: {\n      ansible = {\n        ansible = {\n          path = \"ansible\"\n        },\n        executionEnvironment = {\n          enabled = false\n        },\n        python = {\n          interpreterPath = \"python\"\n        },\n        validation = {\n          enabled = true,\n          lint = {\n            enabled = true,\n            path = \"ansible-lint\"\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n```\nI don't have any overrides for `ansiblels`; this seems to be coming from the `lspconfig` plugin.",
