        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Firstly, a warning is just a warning. checkhealth is trying to give a hint about a potential problem.\n\nSecondly, this particular warning seems relevant since `yaml.ansible` is the only filetype defined by the `ansiblels` config: https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/8e2084bf5e40c79c1f42210a6ef96a0a4793a763/lsp/ansiblels.lua#L36\n\nAs a user of ansible, it's up to you to decide if this matters to you. The config provided by nvim-lspconfig won't automatically attach if it can't find a `yaml.ansible` filetype. \n\n- If it's working for you anyway, that means either:\n    - the filetype is defined by `vim.filetype.add` but checkhealth doesn't see it 😞  . See https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38082\n    - you have some other plugin like mason, doing god-knows-what. \n- If it's *not* working, then that suggests you may need a plugin or personal config that defines an `yaml.ansible` filetype.\n",
